President Muhammadu
Buhari has approved the appointment of Dr (Mrs) Sarah Omotunde Alade, as
Special Adviser to the President on Finance and the Economy, domiciled in the
Ministry of Finance, Budget and National Planning. Malam Garba
Shehu, Senior Special Assistant to
the President (Media & Publicity)
announced this appointment in a statement Tuesday. Dr. Alade, who holds
BSc (Economics) and PhD in Management Science (Operations Research), retired
from the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) as Deputy Governor in 2017 after
spending 23 years in the apex bank. She had also acted
briefly in 2014 as the CBN Governor.